  "prompt": "What do Pakistani citizens think about Uri Attack?",
  "response": "The opinions of Pakistani citizens regarding the Uri Attack, which occurred in September 2016 when Indian soldiers were killed in an attack on an army base in Uri, Jammu and Kashmir, can vary widely. Some may express solidarity with the Indian military in terms of condemning terrorism, while others might view the incident through a political lens, seeing it as a reflection of the ongoing tensions between India and Pakistan.\n\nIn general, public sentiment may hinge on various factors, including nationalistic feelings, personal experiences, or media portrayal. Many Pakistani citizens might also feel that incidents like the Uri Attack perpetuate a cycle of violence and distrust between the two countries.\n\nThe situation is further complicated by differing narratives and the role of media in shaping public perception. Some may perceive the response from their government and military regarding the incident as crucial, while others may call for peace and dialogue.\n\nUltimately, any generalization would be an oversimplification, as attitudes can differ not only based on political views but also regional, ethnic, and personal experiences.",
